1. Matrixport: Liquidity improves but meme coins cool down, Bitcoin market risks still exist;
2. Hyperliquid 50x leveraged whale 20x long LINK was liquidated, losing $1.076 million;
3. Hyperliquid 50x leveraged whale opened LINK long positions again, average opening price: $14.03, liquidation price: $13.32;
4. Zhu Su accused FTX of illegally liquidating 3AC assets and called for SBF to be sentenced to 250 years in prison;
5. Ark Invest increased its position in Coinbase again, increasing its holdings worth $5.2 million;
6. RedotPay completed $40 million in Series A financing, led by Lightspeed;
7. CryptoQuant founder Ki Young Ju: It is too early to assert that we are entering a bear market;
8. In Q1 2025, the financing of the US AI field reached $20 billion, far ahead of the $861 million in the crypto industry;
9. IRISnet plans to upgrade the mainnet 4.0 on March 30, introducing cross-chain NFT functions;
10. Trader Eugene: ETH has been removed from the portfolio, SOL's key support level is $80, and BTC is expected to be supported in the range of $74,000 to $76,000;
11. Russia uses cryptocurrencies in its oil trade with India to circumvent Western sanctions;
12. Crypto.com has obtained a derivatives license issued by the UAE Virtual Asset Regulatory Authority (VARA).
